### DSPy ReAct Endpoint — Request Payloads (all scenarios)
### Compatible with VS Code REST Client / IntelliJ HTTP Client
### Base URL: http://localhost:8000
### Endpoint:  POST /dspy/chat/completions
###
### Notes:
### - The DSPy endpoint accepts the SAME ChatCompletionRequest schema
###   as /v1/chat/completions, BUT internally only uses `model`,
###   `messages`, and `stream`.
### - Tools (weather, email) are loaded server-side from the tool registry
###   and exposed to the ReAct agent automatically — you do NOT pass
###   `tools` in the request body for DSPy.
### - `temperature`, `max_tokens`, `top_p`, `stop`, `frequency_penalty`,
###   `presence_penalty`, `tool_choice`, `tools` are accepted by the
###   schema but ignored by the DSPy route. They are included below
###   only to show they don't break the request.
### - `reasoning_effort` is IGNORED on this endpoint — for Reasoning
###   Language Model runs use POST /rlm/chat/completions instead
###   (see app/test/rlm_requests.http).
### ============================================================


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 1a. Minimal Payload — Non-Streaming (stream omitted → false)
### Uses DEFAULT_MODEL from .env
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the capital of Japan?"
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 1b. Minimal Payload — Streaming
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the capital of Japan?"
    }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 2. Basic Chat — Non-Streaming, model specified
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Explain what ReAct (Reasoning + Acting) is in 2 sentences."
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 3. Basic Chat — Streaming (SSE)
### DSPy executes fully, then the answer is streamed word-by-word
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "List three benefits of using DSPy."
    }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 4. Tool Use — Weather (agent calls get_weather internally)
### No `tools` field needed — DSPy loads them from the registry.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the current weather in Mumbai?"
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 5. Tool Use — Weather (Streaming)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Tell me the weather in Delhi right now."
    }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 6a. Tool Use — Email — Non-Streaming
### Agent calls generate_email internally (no `tools` field needed)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Draft a formal email to john@example.com about the project deadline being extended by one week."
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 6b. Tool Use — Email — Streaming
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Draft a formal email to john@example.com about the project deadline being extended by one week."
    }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 7a. Multi-Tool Reasoning — Non-Streaming
### Agent should pick BOTH weather + email tools across iterations.
### Email address is explicit (jaydip@example.com) — the
### generate_email tool requires `to`, so vague names like "jaydip"
### will cause the model to skip the email step.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Check the weather in Ahmedabad, then draft a casual email to team@company.com suggesting whether tomorrow is a good day for an outdoor team lunch."
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 7b. Multi-Tool Reasoning — Streaming
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Check the weather in Ahmedabad, then draft a casual email to team@company.com suggesting whether tomorrow is a good day for an outdoor team lunch."
    }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 7c. Knowledge + Tool — Capital + Email (Non-Streaming)
### Mirrors a real multi-part prompt: answer one part from model
### knowledge AND call generate_email for the other part. Use a
### concrete email address — the tool's `to` field is required.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the capital of Japan? Also, generate a formal email to jaydip@example.com with the subject 'About Tokyo' explaining that Tokyo is the capital of Japan."
    }
  ],
  "stream": false
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 7d. Knowledge + Tool — Capital + Email (Streaming)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the capital of Japan? Also, generate a formal email to jaydip@example.com with the subject 'About Tokyo' explaining that Tokyo is the capital of Japan."
    }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 8a. Chat with System Prompt — Non-Streaming
### DSPy reads the LAST user message — system messages are kept in
### `messages` but only the latest user content drives the agent.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a concise technical assistant. Keep answers under 3 sentences."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is a vector database?"
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 8b. Chat with System Prompt — Streaming
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a concise technical assistant. Keep answers under 3 sentences."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is a vector database?"
    }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 9a. Multi-Turn Conversation — Non-Streaming
### NOTE: DSPy uses ONLY the last user message
### (see get_last_user_message in dspy_react_service.py).
### Prior turns are ignored by the agent.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My name is Jaydip."
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nice to meet you, Jaydip!"
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the weather in Surat?"
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 9b. Multi-Turn Conversation — Streaming
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My name is Jaydip."
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nice to meet you, Jaydip!"
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the weather in Surat?"
    }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 10a. Different Model — GPT-4o Mini — Non-Streaming
### `openrouter/` prefix is added automatically by normalize_model()
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "openai/gpt-4o-mini",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the weather in London?"
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 10b. Different Model — GPT-4o Mini — Streaming
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "openai/gpt-4o-mini",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is the weather in London?"
    }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 11a. Model with explicit openrouter/ prefix — Non-Streaming
### Should work identically to the unprefixed form (idempotent)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "openrouter/meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Say hello in one short sentence."
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 11b. Model with explicit openrouter/ prefix — Streaming
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "openrouter/meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Say hello in one short sentence."
    }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 12a. Full Payload — Non-Streaming
### ALL parameters the schema accepts. DSPy ignores temperature,
### tools, tool_choice, etc., but the request must still validate.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a helpful assistant that uses tools when appropriate."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What's the weather in Jaipur, and email a summary to manager@company.com?"
    }
  ],
  "stream": false,
  "temperature": 0.7,
  "max_tokens": 500,
  "top_p": 0.9,
  "frequency_penalty": 0.2,
  "presence_penalty": 0.1,
  "stop": ["END"],
  "tool_choice": "auto",
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "city": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "The city name to get weather for"
            }
          },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "generate_email",
        "description": "Generate a formatted email with the given recipient, subject, and optional tone",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "to": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Email recipient address"
            },
            "subject": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Email subject line"
            },
            "tone": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Tone of the email (e.g. formal, casual)",
              "default": "formal"
            }
          },
          "required": ["to", "subject"]+
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 12b. Full Payload — Streaming
### Same as 12a, but with stream=true
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a helpful assistant that uses tools when appropriate."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What's the weather in Jaipur, and email a summary to manager@company.com?"
    }
  ],
  "stream": true,
  "temperature": 0.7,
  "max_tokens": 500,
  "top_p": 0.9,
  "frequency_penalty": 0.2,
  "presence_penalty": 0.1,
  "stop": ["END"],
  "tool_choice": "auto",
  "tools": [
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "get_weather",
        "description": "Get current weather information for a given city",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "city": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "The city name to get weather for"
            }
          },
          "required": ["city"]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "function",
      "function": {
        "name": "generate_email",
        "description": "Generate a formatted email with the given recipient, subject, and optional tone",
        "parameters": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "to": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Email recipient address"
            },
            "subject": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Email subject line"
            },
            "tone": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Tone of the email (e.g. formal, casual)",
              "default": "formal"
            }
          },
          "required": ["to", "subject"]
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 13. Edge Case — Empty user content (Non-Streaming)
### Service should return "No question found." per
### get_last_user_message() fallback.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a helpful assistant."
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 14a. Edge Case — Reasoning without tools — Non-Streaming
### Agent should answer directly without invoking weather/email
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is 17 multiplied by 23?"
    }
  ]
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 14b. Edge Case — Reasoning without tools — Streaming
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "What is 17 multiplied by 23?"
    }
  ],
  "stream": true
}

### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### 15. Auth Header Example (only needed if PROXY_API_KEY is set)
### Uncomment Authorization line on a server with auth enabled.
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST http://localhost:8000/dspy/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json
# Authorization: Bearer your-proxy-api-key-here

{
  "model": "meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Ping."
    }
  ]
}
